This looks fine. Once you fix the DCO I can merge it. See the steps for fixing it [here](https://github.com/hyperledger/ursa/pull/5/checks)

+1

Thanks for updating the docs.  In the future I'd like to see us use a more robust file integrity mechanism.  Something like [minisign](https://jedisct1.github.io/minisign/) or the OpenBSD signify tool.

This is, in general, a good change.  But why is the checksum using a SHA-1 hash instead of a more modern (and less broken) hash function?

And +1 to Dave.  We will need a more robust tool in the long run.
